Additional Notes: - Closed if temperatures are below 45 degrees

Additional Notes:
- Clients must register their first time at the pantry and will be assigned two days per month to pick up food
- ID preferred, but not required
- Only accepts non-perishable food donations, must be packaged or completely sealed

Name: Met Council on Jewish Poverty
Additional Notes:
- Clients may pickup food from the pantry once a month
- Hours are for first-time clients and for those not placing online orders
- ID appreciated, not required 
- Runs on a digital ordering system, place an order online and pick up food on the days you choose. You still need to come to sign up on a Tuesday or Thursday if you are a first time client.

Additional Notes:
- Check website for current schedule

Name: Shiloh Temple Pentecostal Church - Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Can use Plentiful app to reserve time slots in advance.
- ID recommended, but no one will be refused.

Name: Iris House, East Side
Additional Notes:
- Can make an appointment for food bank on the Plentiful app
- Hot meals and lunches Tuesday-Friday 12:00PM-1:30PM
- Fresh market with produce on Wednesday 12:00PM-2:00PM

Name: Dear Mama
Additional Notes:
- Can contact the restaurant if in need of a free meal
- Runs through Upper Manhattan Mutual Aid

Name: Bay Ridge Center - Food Pantry
Additional Notes: - Call to schedule a time to pick up food

Name: South Shore Food Pantry - St. Paul's
Additional Notes:
- Call on Saturday to schedule an appointment

Name: St. Mary's Episcopal Church - Soup Kitchen
Additional Notes:
- Call on Mondays for the location of the mobile soup kitchen
- Please bring your own bags or cart

Name: YWCA Queens
Additional Notes:
- Call listed number on Thursday to make an appointment for the following Wednesday
- ID required for first time

Name: Bronx Academy for Multi Media
Additional Notes:
- By invite only and serving members of school area only.
- Serves residents of zip codes 10474 and 10459
- Food availability depends on delivery supply. Please call before visiting to learn if and when food is available.

Name: The Table at the Family Support Center at NYU Langone
Additional Notes:
- By appointment only. To make an appointment, call (718) 630-7186.
- ID can be provided within 30 days of visit
- Open to anyone in New York

Name: Jewish Community Council (JCC) of Washington Heights & Inwood
Additional Notes:
- By appointment only. Call to schedule an appointment
- ID and proof of address is required to sign up

Name: Immaculate Conception Church
Additional Notes:
- By appointment only. Call to make an appointment. Can also visit during the week to make an appointment and get information on SNAP.
- Eligibility requirement:  Bronx residents

Name: Restore Unity Foundation
Additional Notes: - By appointment only. Call listed number to make an appointment.

Name: New York City Relief, Salvation Army, New York Temple - Food Pantry

Name: La Jornada, Flushing - Food Pantry
Additional Notes: - By appointment only. Call (929) 300-7068 to schedule an appointment.

Name: Resurrection and Life Pentecostal Church
Additional Notes: - Bring your own bag

- Bring proof of address and be prepared to declare income
- Brown bag lunch is for homeless community members

Name: Harlem Dowling West Side Center/Specialized Services
Additional Notes:
- Bring ID or other proof of address  
- Line up at 9AM for the best chance of receiving food

Name: Stapleton U.A.M.E. Church - Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Bring ID for each member of household
- Non-perishable items

Name: New Life SDA Church
Additional Notes:
- Bring ID and verify family size or insurance card
- Accepts food donations only from organizations, not private citizens

Name: Bethlehem Nation's Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Bring ID and registration will be onsite
- Pantry entrance is around the corner from the church on Vermont Street
- Please bring your own bags or cart

Name: V.E.T.S. Inc., - Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Basic photo ID needed to identify patron in case of language barrier
    - There may be exceptions, but generally advised to carry ID. 
- People begin lining up around 8am.

Name: V.E.T.S. Inc., Springfield Gardens
Additional Notes:
- Basic photo ID needed to identify patron in case of language barrier
    - There may be exceptions, but generally advised to carry ID. 
- Military members and veterans can get help
- Hot meals for the homeless
- may offer Boxed stuffing, Rice, paper goods, soap, detergent, showers for veterans

Name: V.E.T.S. Inc., Hollis Gardens
Additional Notes:
- Basic photo ID needed to identify patron in case of language barrier
- Photo ID showing date of birth is required for Senior Silver Service
- Halal and kosher food available when in stock

Name: V.E.T.S. Inc./Taurus Associates, Inc.
Additional Notes:
- Basic photo ID needed to identify patron in case of language barrier
- Kosher and halal available depending on donations

Name: The Red Door Place (Hope for Our Neighbors in Need) - Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Bags given at the 7th Avenue door are for those who are able to cook
- Bags given at the 13th Avenue door are for those who want "no cook" items
- need appointment through plentiful, if not you can still come but at 4:30PM

Name: All Saints Episcopal Church
Additional Notes: - Bagged lunches to go

Name: Temple Shaaray Tefila
Additional Notes:
- Bagged lunches given out on sidewalk
- Prepared Kosher style but food is NOT Kosher
- If no meals, $5 gift certificates will be handed out instead
- Line starts 11:15

Name: Brooklyn College Campus Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Available only to Brooklyn College students
- Visit their website to make appointment

Name: Brooklyn College Campus Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Available only to Brooklyn College Community students
- 312 Student Center Building
- Visit their website to make appointment or email

Name: Health Essential Association, CPMM
Additional Notes: - Available for people in the area

Name: Jewish Community Council (JCC) of Staten Island
Additional Notes:
- Available by appointment only through the Plentiful app.
- First-time clients must bring an ID

Name: Department of Probation, Staten Island
Additional Notes: - Availability of Kosher and Halal varies

Name: Open Door to Heaven Outreach Ministry Inc.
Additional Notes: - Arriving early is recommended to avoid long lines

Name: Crown Heights Community Outreach Center/Church of God of Prophecy
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early to get a ticket
- first come first serve

Name: Macedonia Community Development Corp - Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early to avoid long lines
- Sometimes serve food until 4pm depending on the amount of people

Name: South Jamaica Cornerstone Community Center
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early to avoid long lines
- Sometimes distribution will take place at their other location, 108-41 159th st, right around the corner 
- once a month cooked halal food(thrid Wednesdays of the month)

Name: Little Jerusalem House of Prayer
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early to avoid long lines
- ID is only required if picking up food for someone else

Name: Iglesia de Dios de la Profecia
Additional Notes: - Arrive early to avoid long lines

Name: AIDS Center of Queens County, Far Rockaway
Additional Notes: - Arrive early for the best chance of receiving food. Distributes 80 bags.

Name: Our Lady Charity for the Community Inc
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early for the best chance of receiving food
- Please bring your own bags or cart
- Kosher food are only available sometimes
- Call before to make sure the pantry has enough food to serve (if they don't they will not be open)

Name: SAPNA Emergency Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early for the best chance of receiving food
- Opening time depends on how supplies last
- Register in advance for bags, but the food is always available regardless
- Please bring your own bags or cart
- All vegetables

Name: St. Charles Borromeo Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early for the best chance of receiving food
- Must bring proof of address and photo ID
- Text message system to alert customers if pantry is closed/open

Name: Riverdale Osborne - Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early for the best chance of receiving food
- Bring your own bags or cart

Name: Jewish Community Council (JCC) of Pelham Parkway, Bronx
Additional Notes:
- Arrive early for best chance of receiving food
- Please bring your own bags and cart
- They offer dried/canned goods

Name: Community Services Housing Development Corp. (former William L. Chisolm HDFC)
Additional Notes:
- Arrive before 10AM to get in line, for best chance of receiving food
- Client choice pantry
- Please bring your own bag or cart

Name: Jewish Institute of Queens
Additional Notes:
- Arrive at 10AM for best chance of getting food
- need to fill out form for first time
- need to sign in every time

Name: Glover Memorial Baptist Church - Food Pantry
Additional Notes: - Arrive an hour early to ensure best chance of receiving food

Name: Rauschenbusch Metro Ministries, Inc.
Additional Notes:
- Appointments must be made through the Plentiful App
- Formal ID required 
- To make a weekday Food Pantry appointment with the Plentiful system, please text “FOOD” to “PANTRY” (726-879) or email food@rmmnyc.org or call (212) 594-4464
- Grab-and-go bags are pre-bagged 
- opens 2 times a month
- have some walk in

Name: First Presbyterian Church in Jamaica - Food Pantry
Additional Notes:
- Appointments can be made with the Plentiful app and are served first
- Walk-ins are welcome, just need to show valid ID and proof of address

Name: Food Justice Ministry
Additional Notes:
- Appointments can be made via the Plentiful app.
- Donations of fresh foods & non-perishables allowed
- Do NOT accept canned, processed, or sugary foods
- Donations accepted Tuesdays 6:00pm-7:30pm

Name: Five Loaves and Two Fish Food Pantry, Leviticus Church of God in Christ
Additional Notes:
- Appointments available on Plentiful
- Please bring your own bags or cart
- This location has boxed and canned goods, fresh vegetables and fruits, and bread and dairy products

Name: City Harvest Mobile Market, Queensbridge
Additional Notes:

- ID is required, but there are no neighborhood restrictions
- Located in the basketball court directly behind the Jacob A. Riis Neighborhood Settlement House

Name: LSS/Bethany Lutheran Church
Additional Notes: - Appointments are available to avoid the regular line - Please call 917-533-1679 to guarantee a bag

Name: Church of God in Christ Jesus
Additional Notes: - Anyone who expresses a need for food will be accommodated

Name: Holy Apostles - Soup Kitchen
Additional Notes:
